String:
{ACCURACY} decides how well a character hits their target.
The total amount is added to the base accuracy of skills.
How resistant this character is to {LIGHTNING_DAMAGE}. Also reduces the chance of getting shocked.

How resistant the character is to Bleeding.
Reduces the likelihood of Bleeding.

How likely a character blocks a skill.
The total accuracy is reduced by this amount.

{BRAVERY} is a measure for how well an Adventurer can go beyond their limit.
The higher the {BRAVERY} the more likely the Adventurer survives an otherwise deadly strike. Also increases the BP gain in battle by 1 for every 20 points.

Willpower measures a character's bravery and their ability to lead.
Every point above 5 increases Bravery by 1.
Every 3 points above 5 increases Crit Chance by 1.

Crit Chance dictates how likely a Skill critically succeeds.
Arcane and Divine Skills cannot usually crit.
Every point equals 1% and is added to the base crit chance of a Skill.
How resistant this character is to Dark Damage.

Dexterity is a measure of a character's agility.
Every point above 5 increases {ACCURACY} by 1.
Every 2 points above 5 increases {DODGE} by 1.
Every 4 points above 5 increases {INITIATIVE} by 1.

How likely a character dodges a hostile skill.
The accuracy of a skill is reduced by this amount.
How resistant this character is to Earth Damage. Also reduces the chance of getting staggered.
How resistant this character is to Fire Damage. Also reduces the chance of getting burned.

The total amount of Hitpoints of a character.
If this value reaches zero the character dies.
How resistant this character is to Holy Damage.

Intelligence determines how learned a character is.
Every point above 5 increases Magical Attack Bonus (MAB) by 1.

Magical Attack Bonus dictates the Magical Damage Output of the character.
It is used as a scale for most arcane and divine skills.
SP is sometimes required to use a skill. Most arcane and divine skills use up SP.
How far this Character can move with a move action.

Physical Attack Bonus dictates the physical Damage output of the Character. 
It is used as a scale for most physical Skills.
How resistant this character is to Physical Damage.

How resistant the character is to Poison.
Reduces the likelihood of getting poisoned.

The Initiative stat dictates how fast a character acts.
The higher the Initiative the likelier the character acts first.

Strength is a measure of physical prowess.
Every point above 5 increases Physical Attack Bonus(PAB) by 1.
How resistant the character is to mind-affecting effects like stuns, charm and sleep.
Talent: Growth of this attribute is boosted by an additional 30.
How resistant this character is to Ice Damage. Also reduces the chance of getting chilled or frozen.

Wisdom represents a character's mental fortitude and perceptiveness.
Every point above 5 increases SP by 2 and mind resistance by 1.

More likely to spot hidden traps during Quests.
How much the bleeding damage inflicted by this adventurer is boosted
How much the poison damage inflicted by this adventurer is boosted
How much the healing potency of this adventurer is boosted
How much the holy damage inflicted by this adventurer is boosted
How much the fire damage inflicted by this adventurer is boosted
How much the earth damage inflicted by this adventurer is boosted
How much the lightning damage inflicted by this adventurer is boosted
How much the dark damage inflicted by this adventurer is boosted
How much physical resistance is ignored when dealing physical damage. (Flat reduction)
How much of the relevant resistance is ignored when dealing earth/fire/ice/lightning/dark/holy damage. (Flat reduction)
How much fire resistance is ignored when dealing fire damage. (Flat reduction)
How much earth resistance is ignored when dealing earth damage. (Flat reduction)
How much lightning resistance is ignored when dealing lightning damage. (Flat reduction)
How much ice resistance is ignored when dealing ice damage. (Flat reduction)

On Entering Tile:
Deal <color=red>27-33 Fire Damage</color> to the unit. 100% Base Chance to gain the <color=orange>Burned</color> status
